      • getDerivedUnits

        public java.lang.String getDerivedUnits​()
        Derives the unit of this Species.

        If the model that contains this Species already contains a unit that is equivalent to the derived unit, the corresponding identifier will be returned. In case that the unit cannot be derived or that no equivalent unit exists within the model, or if the model has not been defined yet, null will be returned. In case that this quantity represents a basic Unit.Kind this method will return the String representation of this Unit.Kind.

        In the specific case of a Species, if hasOnlySubstanceUnits is set to false the method will always return null so prefer to use the method getDerivedUnitDefinition() which will return a the right result in this case.

        Specified by:
        getDerivedUnits in interface SBaseWithDerivedUnit
        Overrides:
        getDerivedUnits in class AbstractNamedSBaseWithUnit
        Returns:
        a String that represent the id of a UnitDefinition. This UnitDefinition represent the derived unit of this quantity. If it is not possible to derive a unit for this quantity or if no equivalent UnitDefinition can be found in the Model, null is returned.
        See Also:
        AbstractNamedSBaseWithUnit.getDerivedUnits()

      • getSpatialSizeUnits

        @Deprecated
public java.lang.String getSpatialSizeUnits​()
        Deprecated. Only valid for SBML Level 2 Versions 1 and 2.
        Returns the spatialSizeUnits of this Species.

        If determined, this method first checks the explicitly set spatial size units of this Species. If no such value is defined, it will return the units of the surrounding Compartment. Only if this is also not possible, an empty String will be returned.

        Returns:
        the spatialSizeUnits of this Species.

      • getSpatialSizeUnitsInstance

        @Deprecated
public UnitDefinition getSpatialSizeUnitsInstance​()
        Deprecated. Only valid for SBML Level 2 Versions 1 and 2.
        Returns the spatialSizeUnits UnitDefinition instance of this Species.

        Determines the spatial units of this Species. If the spatial units have been set explicitly using 'spatialSizeUnits' the corresponding UnitDefinition from the Model to which this Species belongs will be returned. Otherwise, the size unit from the surrounding Compartment of this Species will be returned. If this also fails, null will be returned.

        Returns:
        The UnitDefinition instance which as the 'spatialSizeUnits' of this Species as id or the size unit of the surrounding Compartment. null if it doesn't exist.
